    <note>Fang(1) Jun(2) [11411] A Fang(1) Quan [12484] (with same characters) as the great grandson of Jun's brother, Jiao [11412], was jinshi in 1175 and was identified as the great grandson of Cipeng [11228] in Fujian TZ, 147.12a [see funerary inscription for this Quan's son, Shenquan [11427]]. A son of the Quan identified as the great grandson of Cipeng, Chuang [12623], has the same generational name as a son of another son of Quan, Shen(2) [20297], whose ancestor is identified as Jiao. In addition, a lineage decendant of Cipeng, Rong [11289] of the same generation of both Quan and a Hao [11425] has the same generational name. I conclude that this Fang(1) lineage was a branch of lineage 150 and thereby a Shejun Fang(1), and that Fujian TZ means that Quan was a great grandnephew of Cipeng. In other words, Cipeng was a lineage cousin of Jun(2) and Jiao, and, therefore, Jun(2) and Jiao were lineage nephews of Yong [11382]. CBD, 1, 54.</note>
